---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import DurationSpectrumChart from '../../components/basics/inline/DurationSpectrumChart';
import StorageTechCards from '../../components/basics/inline/StorageTechCards';
import StorageScenarioBuilder from '../../components/basics/labs/StorageScenarioBuilder';
import StorageComparisonTool from '../../components/basics/labs/StorageComparisonTool';
import MobileVizFallback from '../../components/MobileVizFallback';
import InfoPanel from '../../components/InfoPanel.astro';
import { url } from '../../utils/url';

const sections = [
  { id: 'duration-problem', title: 'The Duration Problem' },
  { id: 'storage-zoo', title: 'The Storage Zoo' },
  { id: 'scenario-builder', title: 'Pick Your Storage', interactive: true },
  { id: 'comparison-tool', title: 'Compare Technologies', interactive: true },
];
---

<ContentLayout title="Beyond Lithium-Ion" description="Lithium-ion batteries dominate headlines, but the future grid needs a whole portfolio of storage technologies." sections={sections}>

<h1>Beyond Lithium-Ion</h1>

<p class="text-xl" style="color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 600px;">
  Lithium-ion dominates short-duration storage. But the grid needs hours, days, and
  even seasons of stored energy. No single battery chemistry can do it all.
</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="duration-problem">The Duration Problem</h2>

<p>
  Li-ion excels at short bursts -- frequency regulation, peak shaving, solar time-shifting.
  But the grid also needs days and weeks of storage. A winter <em>Dunkelflaute</em> can
  suppress wind and solar for two weeks. Li-ion cannot bridge that gap affordably.
</p>

<p>
  The core issue is <strong>cost per duration</strong>. Li-ion stores energy in the same
  cells that deliver power -- double the duration, double the cost. Other technologies
  decouple the two: a separate "tank" holds energy while a smaller "engine" delivers power.
  Bigger tank, longer duration, without multiplying the expensive parts.
</p>

<MobileVizFallback client:visible fallbackSrc="/images/viz/basics-beyond-lithium-ion.png" alt="Storage technology duration spectrum chart">
  <DurationSpectrumChart client:visible />
</MobileVizFallback>

<p>
  No single technology covers the full spectrum. The future grid needs a portfolio --
  fast-response batteries for seconds-to-hours, medium-duration storage for daily
  cycling, and long-duration options that can bridge weeks of low renewable output.
</p>

<h2 id="storage-zoo">The Storage Zoo</h2>

<p>
  Researchers and engineers are working on dozens of storage technologies. Seven have
  emerged as serious contenders, each with a different sweet spot on the duration
  spectrum. Click any card below to learn how it works.
</p>

<StorageTechCards client:visible />

<h2 id="scenario-builder">Pick Your Storage</h2>

<p>
  Build a storage portfolio by mixing technologies. See how different combinations
  cover the duration spectrum.
</p>

<MobileVizFallback client:visible fallbackSrc="/images/viz/basics-beyond-lithium-ion.png" alt="Storage scenario builder">
  <StorageScenarioBuilder client:visible />
</MobileVizFallback>

<h2 id="comparison-tool">Compare Technologies</h2>

<p>
  Select technologies to compare their key characteristics side by side.
</p>

<MobileVizFallback client:visible fallbackSrc="/images/viz/basics-beyond-lithium-ion.png" alt="Storage technology comparison tool">
  <StorageComparisonTool client:visible />
</MobileVizFallback>

<div class="my-8 flex flex-col gap-4">
  <InfoPanel label="GO DEEPER">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <a href={url("/research/topics/grid-flexibility-costs")} class="text-base font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">Grid Flexibility Costs</a>
      <a href={url("/research/topics/demand-response")} class="text-base font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">Demand Response</a>
    </div>
  </InfoPanel>
</div>

</ContentLayout>
